LeetCode 424. Longest Repeating Character Replacement
Problem
Given a string s and an integer k, you can replace at most k characters. Find the length of the longest substring that can be transformed into a string with all identical characters.

Example:
s = "ABAB", k = 2
Output = 4

Replace both 'A's with 'B' (or vice versa).
1. Brute Force

For every starting index i, extend the substring to the right. Keep track of the frequency of characters and the maximum frequency (maxFreq) in the current substring.

A substring is valid if:

windowLength - maxFreq <= k

because all characters except the most frequent one need to be replaced.

Time Complexity
Outer loop: O(n)
Inner loop: O(n)
Update frequency: O(1)

Total: O(n²)

Code
class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {

        int n = s.length();
        int ans = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            int[] freq = new int[26];
            int maxFreq = 0;

            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {

                freq[s.charAt(j) - 'A']++;
                maxFreq = Math.max(maxFreq,
                                   freq[s.charAt(j) - 'A']);

                int windowLength = j - i + 1;

                if (windowLength - maxFreq <= k) {
                    ans = Math.max(ans, windowLength);
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
2. Optimal: Dynamic Sliding Window
Key Observation

For any window:

windowLength = j - i + 1
maxFreq = frequency of the most common character

The number of replacements needed is:

replacements = windowLength - maxFreq

If:

windowLength - maxFreq > k

then the window is invalid, so shrink it from the left.

Algorithm
Expand the window by moving j.
Update the frequency of s[j].
Update maxFreq.
While (windowLength - maxFreq) > k, shrink the window by moving i.
Keep track of the maximum valid window length.
Code (Optimal)
class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {

        int[] freq = new int[26];

        int i = 0;
        int maxFreq = 0;
        int ans = 0;

        for (int j = 0; j < s.length(); j++) {

            freq[s.charAt(j) - 'A']++;

            maxFreq = Math.max(maxFreq,
                               freq[s.charAt(j) - 'A']);

            while ((j - i + 1) - maxFreq > k) {
                freq[s.charAt(i) - 'A']--;
                i++;
            }

            ans = Math.max(ans, j - i + 1);
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
