Maximum valid window length = 4.

Note: maxFreq is never decreased when the left pointer moves. This is intentional and still gives the correct answer because it only delays shrinking; it never causes us to miss the optimal window.

Why This Formula Works

Suppose the current window is:

A A B A B

Frequency:

A = 3
B = 2

To make all characters the same:

Convert both Bs into As.
Required replacements = 2.

This equals:

windowLength - maxFreq
= 5 - 3
= 2

So the validity condition is:

(windowLength - maxFreq) <= k
