Pattern to Remember

Many dynamic sliding window problems follow this structure:

for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
    // include nums[j] / s.charAt(j)

    while (window is invalid) {
        // remove nums[i] / s.charAt(i)
        i++;
    }

    // update answer
}

For LeetCode 424, the window is invalid when:

(window size - maximum frequency character in window) > k

This is the core idea to remember.
